Sean Terkildsen
Hi there,
Vehicle has a oil pressure circuit code, following diagnostic procedure requires tech to remove upper and lower intake manifold to gain access to oil filter housing unit. The oil pressure sensor is built onto that housing. Tech will then check circuit from sensor to PCM to ensure there is no damage to wiring (broken wires, short to ground, short to power, excessive resistance, etc). If all checks wiring out vehicle will require new oil pressure sensor and relearn. reassembly of intake manifold will require new upper and lower intake seal as they are one time use. 
Best wishes,​
James Young | Service Advisor
